  "body": "“Dinner over, we produced a bundle of pens, a copious supply of ink, and a goodly show of writing and blotting paper. For there was something very comfortable in having plenty of stationery.”\r\n\r\n—Charles Dickens, Great Expectations\r\n\r\nStationery Store FavoritesWe’ve gathered some of our best-loved notecards, stationery, greeting cards, and other indispensable items found in fine stationery stores.       Shop The Reader’s Catalog [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/the-readers-catalog]\r\n\r\nPure Cotton Notecard Presentation Box\r\n\r\nPure Cotton stationery is made without any chemicals. This handsome presentation box is embellished with a rich, gold “Pure Cotton” label and stores fifty classic 4\" x 6\" flat notecards and fifty matching envelopes lined with white tissue paper. Creamy white, with a soft woven finish, the cards are ideal for writing with a fountain pen, a rollerball, or a ballpoint. This is a wonderful set to have on hand or an elegant, thoughtful gift.\r\n\r\nVintage-Inspired [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/vintage-inspired?_pos=1&_psq=vintage&_ss=e&_v=1.0]\r\n\r\n“Life is Difficult” Peanuts Cards\r\n\r\nShare the humor of life’s difficult moments with these letterpress cards featuring an original comic strip from Charles M. Schulz’s beloved Peanuts comics. This strip, first published in 1966, features the sardonic wit that has made Peanuts’s popularity so enduring. In this strip, Charlie Brown shares his encouraging new philosophy with his pal Linus: “I only dread one day at a time!”\r\n\r\nWry Humor [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/wry-humor?_pos=1&_psq=wry+humor&_ss=e&_v=1.0]\r\n\r\nNature-Inspired\r\n\r\nLetterpress Cards Set\r\n\r\nThis set of ten letterpress cards has been hand-made by American artisans with a charming touch of nostalgia. Having this beautiful set of cards on hand will save you a trip (or ten) to the stationery store. Featuring ten unique designs appropriate for all occasions, the set includes rustic illustrations sure to appeal to nature lovers: Canoe Strokes, Cloud Formations, the Names of the Full Moon, Trail Signs, Animal Tracks in the Snow, Little Homes, Campfires, Tall Peaks, Feet You May Meet, and House Parts.\r\n\r\nScience and Nature [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/science-and-nature?_pos=1&_psq=science+and&_ss=e&_v=1.0]\r\n\r\nThe Natural World\r\n\r\nGreeting Card Collection\r\n\r\nThis collection of eight greeting cards features archival illustrations of colorful fauna, from butterflies to bullfrogs. These vintage images are printed in England on an uncoated, light cream 300 gsm Italian paper, which is recyclable, biodegradable, and FSC certified. Each greeting card is 170 mm x 120 mm (approximately 5\" x 7\"), blank inside, individually wrapped in a compostable wrapper made from plants, and paired with a 100% recycled, 110 gsm kraft envelope.\r\n\r\nScience and Nature [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/science-and-nature?_pos=1&_psq=science+and&_ss=e&_v=1.0]\r\n\r\nEdward Gorey Sparkler\r\n\r\nBirthday Cards\r\n\r\nEdward Gorey (1925–2000) was an American artist, writer, and book designer. His drawings and stories, set in a vaguely Edwardian time frame, exhibit a special genius for what is left unseen and unsaid. Crosshatched characters and quirky narratives keep Gorey devotees in gleeful anticipation of decorous mayhem. Message on front of card: “I hope that you are pleased to see / this card that comes to you from me.” Inside greeting: “Happy Birthday!”\r\n\r\nEdward Gorey [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/edward-gorey]                     Edward Gorey\r\n\r\nBirthday Cake Cards\r\n\r\nWith these notecards on hand, you’ll always be able to send a sweet birthday greeting. From the bow on the cook's apron to the smile on the clock, every detail comes together happily in this celebratory greeting card. Inside greeting: “Happy Birthday!”\r\n\r\nThe creator of more than one hundred works—from a wealth of darkly hilarious books to the animated opening sequence of the PBS television series Mystery!—Gorey was a master of the amusing, the strange, and the unexpected. His artworks are collected and treasured throughout the world.\r\n\r\nGreeting Cards [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/greeting-cards]\r\n\r\nThe Snooty Bookshop Postcards\r\n\r\nThis postcard set celebrates more than a decade of Tom Gauld’s contributions to The Guardian, with fifty of his most beloved strips, from “Procrastination for Creative Writers, a 10-Week Course” and “Poetry Anthologies for People Who Don’t Like Poems” to an alternative bookshop shelving section (“Yes, we do have a copy of the book you’re looking for. You’ll find it in the ‘Vastly Overrated’ section of the ‘So-called Classics’ Department”).\r\n\r\nWry Humor [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/wry-humor?_pos=1&_psq=wry+hu&_ss=e&_v=1.0]\r\n\r\nDisco Ball Correspondence Cards\r\n\r\nAdd some joie de vivre to your correspondence with these all-occasion cards. A shimmering image of a mirrored disco bal in glistening gold is foil-stamped here on heavyweight, cream-colored cardstock. Having these exuberant cards on hand ensures you’ll always be able to promptly send a note to celebrate any event or occasion.\r\n\r\nDesk [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/desk]                     Liberty London Notecard Assortment\r\n\r\n“Liberty is the chosen resort of the artistic shopper.”—Oscar Wilde\r\n\r\nLiberty London, founded in 1875 as an “emporium laden with luxuries and fabrics from distant lands,” is indeed a resort—a haven of sophisticated design, an island of quality, known for both tradition and innovation. This notecard set features eight of Liberty’s heritage floral prints.\r\n\r\nFor the Anglophile [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/for-the-anglophile?_pos=1&_psq=for+the+an&_ss=e&_v=1.0]\r\n\r\nClassic Laid Notecard Presentation Box\r\n\r\nThis handsome presentation box stores fifty pale-blue notecards, with matching envelopes lined with white tissue. The cards have a laid finish (the surface has the appearance of fine lines running the length of the paper) and are compatible with fountain pen, rollerball, or ballpoint.\r\n\r\nTiny Heart Foil- Pressed Notecards\r\n\r\nThese pressed notecards are small and subtle, but they make quite an impression. Neon pink hearts are foil-pressed on heavyweight creamy white cardstock in this set of memorable notecards with coordinating envelopes.\r\n\r\nPure Cotton Correspondence Pad and Envelopes\r\n\r\nThis stationery is as essential and elegant as an impeccably tailored white shirt. Pure Cotton is a paper made without any chemicals. Creamy white, with a soft woven finish and a watermark; ideal for writing with any pen.\r\n\r\nStationery [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/stationery]\r\n\r\nWinnie the Pooh & Friends Card Set\r\n\r\nThis charming set of six letterpress cards features nostalgic scenes and characters from A.A. Milne’s Winnie the Pooh. The greeting cards are designed by William Muller and letterpress printed on fine heavy-weight paper in a studio in Easthampton, Massachusetts.\r\n\r\nJanet All-Occasion Greeting Cards by Glen Baxter\r\n\r\nThese all-occasion cards are sure to enchant both confirmed Baxterians—that is, fans of Glen Baxter, “a kind of mad cross between Magritte, S. J. Perelman, and pulp fiction” (New York Times)—and those in dire need of an introduction.\r\n\r\nThe Glory of Color Greeting Card Collection\r\n\r\nThis collection of five greeting cards features illustrations that accompanied nineteenth- and early-twentieth-century color theories. Capturing every hue in the rainbow, these vintage images are printed in England.\r\n\r\nGreeting Cards [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/greeting-cards]\r\n\r\nGold-Stamped “Merci”\r\n\r\nThank You Cards\r\n\r\nA simple but elegant metallic gold “MERCI” is foil-stamped on these correspondence cards of heavyweight creamy stock. Having these thank you cards on hand ensures always being able to promptly send a note of appreciation.\r\n\r\nFor the Francophile [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/for-the-francophile]\r\n\r\nThe Night Sky Postcard Set\r\n\r\nThis handsome foil-stamped box holds fifty postcards, each with a single sublime image: a page from Galileo’s sketchbook, a Chinese star map, an artist's interpretation of the universe, or a rarely seen image from the NASA archives.\r\n\r\nUnder $25 [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/gifts-under-25?_pos=1&_psq=under+%24&_ss=e&_v=1.0]\r\n\r\nRuler and Letter Opener\r\n\r\nCrafted in Italy from hard-tempered steel, this graceful yet practical tool features a refined gold-plated handle and engraved imperial measurements. A thin layer of 24-karat gold is applied to the letter opener, giving it a beautiful, shining gold finish.\r\n\r\nDesk [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/desk]\r\n\r\nLetter Opener\r\n\r\nAdd an element of old-fashioned elegance to your desk with this letter opener. Crafted in Italy from hard-tempered steel, this graceful yet practical tool features a refined gold-plated curved handle. A thin layer of 24-karat gold is applied to the handle to give it a lustrous finish.\r\n\r\nDesk [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/desk]                         Women in Art Postcard Set\r\n\r\nThis set of postcards features portraits of fifty pioneering female artists by Rachel Ignotofsky, the New York Times bestselling author and illustrator of Women in Art. The 100 postcards celebrate women artists throughout history with vibrant and colorful portraits. Some of the artists are well-known, like the painters Frida Kahlo and Georgia O’Keeffe.\r\n\r\nFor the Art Lover [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/for-the-art-lover]                     Assorted Set of Thank You Cards\r\n\r\nThis set of handmade stationery features a delightfully eclectic set of thank you cards with eleven different designs. With this set on hand, you’re sure to always have a thank you note for any gift you receive. Parcel, the small business that makes these cards, is dedicated “to honoring the beauty of lost arts, crafts and trades.” Every item in this line is either stamped or printed by hand in the studio of the artisan/creator, using vintage or antique imagery or original designs. Made in the USA.\r\n\r\nVintage-Inspired [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/vintage-inspired?_pos=1&_psq=vintage&_ss=e&_v=1.0]                         “Give Us Peace”\r\n\r\nLetterpress Cards\r\n\r\nThis letterpress card is printed with the Latin phrase Dona Nobis Pacem, which may be translated as “Give Us Peace.” The cards are printed in gold foil on 100% cotton, cream-colored matte paper and are blank inside. Each card is accompanied by a matching gold metallic envelope.\r\n\r\nHoliday [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/holiday]                     Animal Tracks in the Snow\r\n\r\nHoliday Cards\r\n\r\nThis letterpress greeting card is perfect for the entire holiday season and beyond. Individual cards are blank inside for your personal message. This guide to identifying animal tracks in the snow was originally published in 1897 by St. Nicholas Magazine­—an American children’s magazine containing works by authors such as Mark Twain and Rudyard Kipling.\r\n\r\nSeasonal [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/seasonal]\r\n\r\nThe Sporting Life Greeting Card Collection\r\n\r\nThis collection of six quaint and colorful greeting cards features archival illustrations of old-school techniques for playing tennis, rugby, golf, and other sports. These images are printed in England on uncoated, light cream 300 gsm Italian paper, which is recyclable, biodegradable, and FSC-certified\r\n\r\nThe Cabinet of Curiosities Greeting Card Collection\r\n\r\nThis collection has twenty-two greeting cards with archival illustrations, curated by our editors. The vintage imagery on these cards ranges in content and style. Some cards are beautiful, some are witty, but all are thought-provoking and memorable.\r\n\r\nThe Architectural Icons Greeting Card Collection\r\n\r\nWhich were the world’s tallest buildings in the nineteenth century? What is the difference between a Tuscan and a Doric column? These six greeting cards feature archival illustrations that answer these and other questions about old-world architecture.\r\n\r\nExclusive to Us [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/exclusive-to-us?_pos=1&_psq=exclus&_ss=e&_v=1.0]\r\n\r\nJames Joyce\r\n\r\nDubliners Cards\r\n\r\n“His soul swooned slowly as he heard the snow falling faintly through the universe.”\r\n\r\nThis quote from James Joyce’s short story “The Dead,” in the collection Dubliners, is printed on pale cream–colored, acid-free stock, 100% recycled, FSC-certified, and carbon-neutral.\r\n\r\nPeace and Goodwill Holiday Cards\r\n\r\nThese cheery blue-and-gold holiday cards are inspired by the David Jones lettering in the permanent collection of Kettle’s Yard, a unique house and gallery with a remarkable collection of twentieth-century art. Kettle’s Yard is a part of the University of Cambridge in England. The greeting on the front reads: “PEACE AND GOODWILL ONE AND ALL.”\r\n\r\nWoody Guthrie’s “New Years Rulin’s” Greeting Cards\r\n\r\nWoody Guthrie wrote these heartfelt and playful resolutions on New Year’s Day, 1943. This little gem, in the middle of the book, provides insight into his daily concerns at the time—the large and the small—and reflects his hopes of being his best before the birth of their first child together.\r\n\r\nStocking Stuffers [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/stocking-stuffers]                      Card Catalog Notecards\r\n\r\nEvoking memories of beautiful wooden card catalogs, this replica sturdy cardboard box comes with a set of thirty flat notecards and envelopes. The front of each card reproduces an original card from the Library of Congress and features a different famous work of literature, such as The Divine Comedy, Little Women, Pride and Prejudice, A Tale of Two Cities, Lady Chatterley’s Lover, Leaves of Grass, and Ulysses.\r\n\r\nLibrary-Themed Gifts [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/library-themed-gifts]                     Assorted Foil Gift Tags\r\n\r\nA whimsical assortment of images has been foil-stamped by hand on these petite, die-cut gift tags to attach to any gift wrap; every charming tag will elevate a simple brown paper bag or bottle of wine to the celebratory. Each set is a unique assortment of styles and foil colors.\r\n\r\nGift Guide [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/gift-guide?_pos=1&_psq=gift+guide&_ss=e&_v=1.0]                         E. Frances Little Notes®\r\n\r\nE. Frances Little Notes® are tiny in size and big on heart. Small enough to slip in a pocket, a lunch box, or a stack of books, each one carries something much larger than its size: a laugh, a love note, a small connection. Whether it’s a joke tucked into a backpack, a to-do list turned sweet, or a simple “thank you,” E. Frances Little Notes® bring joy to life’s little, big, and in-between moments.\r\n\r\nDesk [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/desk]                     Gels™ Manhattan Reading Glasses\r\n\r\nGels® Manhattan reading glasses feature optical-quality lenses with a scratch-resistant coating and thin-rimmed frames made of TR-90 surgical plastic. Choose between black, blue, and tortoiseshell frames and four different strengths of magnification. The frames come in a soft matte texture embellished with working rivets. Cosmopolitan style meets refined functionality in this eyewear.\r\n\r\nSale [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/sale]\r\n\r\nThe New York Review of Books Notebook\r\n\r\nBe ready when inspiration strikes. The New York Review of Books notebook is a portable journal that fits easily in your pocket or purse. This small but sturdy journal has ivory-colored ruled paper, a rigid cover, an elastic closure, and a ribbon bookmark. The New York Review of Books logo is in yellow on a red cover.\r\n\r\nHardcover, 96 ruled pages, 70g lined paper.\r\n\r\nNYR Merchandise [https://shop.nybooks.com/collections/nyr-merchandise]\r\n\r\nYou are receiving this message because you signed up for email newsletters from The New York Review of Books, NYRB, or The Reader’s Catalog. You can  choose the types of mailings you wish to receive https://thenewyorkreview.updatemyprofile.com/y-adhtkuy-36F2A313-iruduywlh-jr.\r\n\r\nUpdate preferences https://thenewyorkreview.updatemyprofile.com/y-adhtkuy-36F2A313-iruduywlh-jy\r\n\r\nThe Reader’s Catalog\r\n\r\n207 East 32nd Street, New York NY 10016\r\n\r\nPreferences https://thenewyorkreview.updatemyprofile.com/y-adhtkuy-36F2A313-iruduywlh-jj  |   Unsubscribe https://email.nybooks.com/t/y-u-adhtkuy-iruduywlh-ji/\r\n",
